\title{Persistent Homology of the Skill Forest}
\taxon{section}
\date{2026-04-04}
\tag{persistent-homology}
\tag{persistence-diagram}
\tag{topological-data-analysis}
\meta{description}{Betti numbers tracked over 1011 commits of plurigrid/asi from 2025-12-17 to 2026-04-04}

\import{macros}

\p{We track the homology of the skill transclusion graph over 10 sampled snapshots of the main branch and 10 parallel branch tips. #{H_0} counts connected components (skills that can reach each other). #{H_1} counts independent cycles (redundant transclusion paths). Orphans are isolated fixed points.}
\p{\strong{Update 2026-06-10, post-mesh.} Recomputed on the current graph: 4120 vertices, 11168 edges, #{H_0 = 4} components, #{H_1 = 7052} cycles, 3 degree-zero orphans. Orphan ratio fell from 64 percent to about zero; slop-flood inflation resolved. Now four connected components.}

\subtree{
\title{Filtration: Main Branch}

\table{
\tr{\th{Date}\th{Skills}\th{Edges}\th{#{H_0}}\th{#{H_1}}\th{Orphans}\th{Connected}\th{Phase}}
\tr{\td{2025-12-17}\td{20}\td{0}\td{20}\td{0}\td{20}\td{0}\td{Dust}}
\tr{\td{2025-12-20}\td{166}\td{147}\td{95}\td{68}\td{93}\td{73}\td{Nucleation}}
\tr{\td{2025-12-24}\td{184}\td{149}\td{112}\td{69}\td{110}\td{74}\td{Plateau}}
\tr{\td{2025-12-25}\td{262}\td{224}\td{157}\td{110}\td{154}\td{108}\td{Growth}}
\tr{\td{2026-01-08}\td{488}\td{571}\td{244}\td{308}\td{240}\td{248}\td{Condensation}}
\tr{\td{2026-02-13}\td{681}\td{749}\td{360}\td{406}\td{358}\td{323}\td{Expansion}}
\tr{\td{2026-04-04}\td{2227}\td{1895}\td{1464}\td{1070}\td{1437}\td{790}\td{Slop flood}}
}

\p{Three distinct phases:}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Nucleation} (Dec 17-20): From 20 disconnected skills to 73 connected with 5 hubs. gay-mcp appears immediately as the dominant attractor with in-degree 20.}
\li{\strong{Condensation} (Dec 25 - Jan 8): Edges overtake vertices (571 > 488). #{H_1} exceeds #{H_0} (308 > 244). The graph becomes more cyclic than treelike — redundant paths form.}
\li{\strong{Slop flood} (Feb 13 - Apr 4): 1546 skills added but only 467 new connections. Orphan ratio jumps from 52\% to 64\%. The bulk import of K-Dense-AI security corpus inflated #{H_0} without adding edges.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Persistence Diagram}

\p{Each feature (component or cycle) has a birth time (when it appears) and death time (when it merges or collapses). Features far from the diagonal are persistent — they are real topological structure. Features near the diagonal are noise.}

\subtree{
\title{#{H_0}: Components}
\pre{\startverb
Death
  ^
  |  
  |           * gay-mcp component (born Dec 17, never dies)
  |         * bisimulation-game (born Dec 20, never dies)
  |        * acsets (born Dec 20, never dies)
  |       * triad-interleave (born Dec 20, never dies)
  |      * spi-parallel-verify (born Dec 25, never dies)
  |
  |  ****  ~1097 orphan components (born, never merge)
  | *****  (cluster on diagonal — born = alive, zero persistence)
  |
  +-------------------------------------------> Birth
   Dec17  Dec20  Dec25  Jan08  Feb13  Apr04

Interpretation:
  - 5 persistent components (the hub attractors) sit FAR from diagonal
  - 1097 orphans sit ON the diagonal (birth = present, never die)
  - The gap between the 5 persistent features and the 1097 noise
    features is the "persistence gap" — it is enormous
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{#{H_1}: Cycles}
\pre{\startverb
Death
  ^
  |
  |  * Main cycle cluster (born Dec 20, 68 initial cycles)
  |    \  grows to 1070 cycles by Apr 04
  |     \  ratio edges:cycles stabilizes at 0.56
  |      \
  |       The H1/edges ratio is the key invariant:
  |       0.46 (Dec 20) -> 0.54 (Jan 08) -> 0.56 (Apr 04)
  |
  |       56% of edges create redundant paths.
  |       The graph is "more loop than tree."
  |
  +-------------------------------------------> Birth
   Dec17  Dec20  Dec25  Jan08  Feb13  Apr04

Interpretation:
  - H1 grows monotonically (cycles never die)
  - The H1/edge ratio converging to ~0.56 means the connected
    component is approaching a "critical cycling" regime
  - Every new edge has a 56% chance of creating a cycle
    rather than connecting a new component
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Hub Attractor Persistence}

\p{9 hubs have appeared in the top-5 across the history. 5 are persistent from birth to present. 4 appeared later.}

\table{
\tr{\th{Hub}\th{Birth}\th{Final In-degree}\th{Persistence}}
\tr{\td{[[gay-mcp]]}\td{2025-12-20}\td{129}\td{\strong{Permanent} — born at nucleation, monotonically increasing}}
\tr{\td{[[bisimulation-game]]}\td{2025-12-20}\td{45}\td{\strong{Permanent} — born at nucleation}}
\tr{\td{[[acsets]]}\td{2025-12-20}\td{37}\td{\strong{Permanent} — born at nucleation}}
\tr{\td{[[triad-interleave]]}\td{2025-12-20}\td{18}\td{\strong{Permanent} — born at nucleation, slower growth}}
\tr{\td{[[three-match]]}\td{2025-12-20}\td{6}\td{Permanent but small — born at nucleation, nearly flat}}
\tr{\td{[[spi-parallel-verify]]}\td{2025-12-25}\td{13}\td{Permanent — born 8 days after nucleation}}
\tr{\td{[[aptos-agent]]}\td{2026-02-13}\td{38}\td{Late entrant — born at expansion phase, rapid growth}}
\tr{\td{[[plurigrid-asi-integrated]]}\td{2026-02-13}\td{31}\td{Late entrant — meta-skill aggregator}}
\tr{\td{[[aptos-society]]}\td{2026-02-13}\td{29}\td{Late entrant — Aptos ecosystem cluster}}
}

\p{The founding pentad (gay-mcp, bisimulation-game, acsets, triad-interleave, three-match) were all born on the same day: 2025-12-20. They are the nucleation seeds. Their persistence is infinite — they have never left the top ranks.}

\p{The Aptos cluster (aptos-agent, aptos-society) appeared 56 days later and grew rapidly, but their in-degree is driven by a different skill population (DeFi/blockchain) than the categorical core.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Branch Divergence}

\p{44 branches exist. All diverged before the April 4 slop flood (+810 skills). Every branch has \em{fewer} skills than main but \em{similar} #{H_1}.}

\table{
\tr{\th{Branch}\th{Skills vs main}\th{#{H_0} vs main}\th{#{H_1} vs main}}
\tr{\td{skill/cyton-dongle}\td{-805}\td{-771}\td{-15}}
\tr{\td{skill/dymaxion-projection}\td{-805}\td{-771}\td{-15}}
\tr{\td{nhero-skills}\td{-811}\td{-728}\td{-195}}
\tr{\td{claude/new-session-UA1Q5}\td{-816}\td{-739}\td{-185}}
}

\p{Key observation: branches lose ~800 skills (the slop) but only ~15 cycles. The connected core's topology is \strong{branch-invariant}. The 242 connected skills and their 1070 cycles exist identically across all branches. Only the orphan mass differs.}

\p{This confirms: the slop flood added vertices without edges. The topological structure of the forest was fixed by January 2026 and has not changed since.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Invariants}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Founding pentad}: gay-mcp, bisimulation-game, acsets, triad-interleave, three-match — born together, persist forever}
\li{\strong{#{H_1}/edges ratio}: converging to 0.56 — the graph's "cycling constant"}
\li{\strong{Connected component size}: ~790 vertices, stable across branches}
\li{\strong{Orphan ratio}: 64\% on main, reflecting bulk import policy not graph structure}
\li{\strong{Persistence gap}: distance from the 5 permanent features to the 1097 ephemeral ones is maximal — there is no intermediate persistence}
}

\p{The persistence diagram is bimodal: either a feature persists forever (the 5 hubs) or it has zero persistence (the 1097 orphans). There is nothing in between. This is the topological signature of a curated core surrounded by unintegrated bulk.}
}
